  "id": "019d3482-45d7-7c41-993a-bcaae10ecde5",
  "content": "# Spoke CLI (Phase 1) — Decision Record (2026-03-28)\n\n## What: Implemented `corvia workspace spoke` subcommand group for managing Docker spoke containers in multi-agent workspaces.\n\n## Key Design Decisions:\n1. Docker labels for stateless tracking (no sidecar state files). spoke list queries Docker directly.\n2. HubContext path resolution uses longest-prefix-match with path boundary enforcement (mount for /data won't match /datafiles).\n3. parse_memory_limit returns Result (not silent fallback) to prevent misconfiguration.\n4. MCP token written outside git tree (~/.claude/.mcp.json) with symlink + git exclude to prevent credential leaks.\n5. Copied instruction files (AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md) added to .git/info/exclude to prevent accidental commits.\n6. Entrypoint uses CORVIA_BRANCH from hub (not self-generated from issue title) for branch name consistency.\n7. Resource limits: memory_swap = memory (no swap), pids_limit = 512, restart on-failure:3.\n8. destroy renamed --force to --immediate for semantic clarity (--force on create means replace).\n\n## Review Findings Worth Remembering:\n- Path boundary enforcement is critical for Docker-from-Docker mount resolution. starts_with alone is insufficient.\n- Silent fallbacks on config parsing (like memory limits) are a dangerous UX pattern. Always error or warn.\n- Any file written inside a git working directory can accidentally be committed. Use git exclude or write outside the tree.\n- Credentials visible via docker inspect is a known limitation of the Docker env var pattern. Document, don't try to fix in Phase 1.\n\n## What Blocked / Surprised:\n- bollard 0.19 API differs from docs in several places: HostConfigLogConfig uses `typ` not `type`, StopContainerOptions requires `signal` field, ContainerSummaryStateEnum doesn't impl Default.\n- Per-spoke agent token registration (bcrypt + coordinator) was deferred to Phase 2 as it requires new dependencies and server-side changes.",
